label.value: SLC4A7 Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in cellular homeostasis.

label.value: Cystic Teratoma
SLC4A7 wt Allele

value.value: Human SLC4A7 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 3p22 and is approximately 137 kb in length. This allele, which encodes sodium bicarbonate cotransporter 3 protein, plays a role in the symport of sodium and bicarbonate ions. Single nucleotide polymorphisms in the gene may contribute to breast cancer susceptibility.

label.value: Sodium Bicarbonate Cotransporter 3

value.value: Sodium bicarbonate cotransporter 3 (1214 aa, ~136 kDa) is encoded by the human SLC4A7 gene. This protein is involved in the regulation of intracellular pH.

label.value: COX11 Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in the mediation of both protein-protein interactions and the mitochondrial respiratory chain.

label.value: COX11 wt Allele

value.value: Human COX11 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17q22 and is approximately 17 kb in length. This allele, which encodes cytochrome c oxidase assembly protein COX11, mitochondrial protein, plays a role in the regulation of cytochrome c oxidation. Single nucleotide polymorphisms in the gene may contribute to breast cancer susceptibility.

label.value: Cytochrome C Oxidase Assembly Protein COX11, Mitochondrial

value.value: Cytochrome c oxidase assembly protein COX11, mitochondrial (276 aa, ~31 kDa) is encoded by the human COX11 gene. This protein is involved in the assembly of cytochrome c oxidase.

label.value: RAD51B Gene

value.value: This gene plays a role in the mediation of homologous recombinational repair of DNA.

label.value: RAD51B wt Allele

value.value: Human RAD51B wild-type allele is located within 14q23-q24.2 and is approximately 776 kb in length. This allele, which encodes DNA repair protein RAD51 homolog 2, is involved in the modulation of DNA repair. Single nucleotide polymorphisms in the gene may contribute to breast cancer susceptibility.

label.value: DNA Repair Protein RAD51 Homolog 2

value.value: DNA repair protein RAD51 homolog 2 (384 aa, ~42 kDa) is encoded by the human RAD51B gene. This protein plays a role in DNA repair.

label.value: NLK Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in the regulation of protein phosphorylation.

label.value: Liver Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of liver cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Intrahepatic bile duct cancers are no longer included in this classification.  The staging of liver cancer now includes only hepatocellular carcinoma. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Mature Teratoma

value.value: A teratoma which may be cystic; it is composed entirely of well differentiated, adult-type mature tissues, without evidence of fetal-type immature tissues (grade 0 teratoma).

label.value: NLK wt Allele

value.value: Human NLK wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17q11.2 and is approximately 154 kb in length. This allele, which encodes serine/threonine protein kinase NLK protein, plays a role in cell fate determination, bone marrow cell differentiation, phosphorylation of transcription factors and Wnt signaling.

label.value: Liver Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of liver cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Complete pathologic staging consists of evaluation of the primary tumor, including histologic grade, regional lymph node status, and underlying liver disease.  Regional lymph node involvement is rare (5%) except in the fibrolamellar variant of hepatocellular carcinoma. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of liver cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Serine/Threonine-Protein Kinase NLK

value.value: Serine/threonine protein kinase NLK (527 aa, ~58 kDa) is encoded by the human NLK gene. This protein is involved in the mediation of protein phosphorylation that affects cellular differentiation, transcription and signal transduction.

label.value: Liver Cancer pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Liver cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Liver cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Liver cancer with solitary tumor without vascular invasion. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: AIDS-Related Oral Cavity Plasmablastic Lymphoma

value.value: A plasmablastic oral mucosa lymphoma in a patient with acquired immunodeficiency syndrome.

label.value: Liver Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Liver cancer with solitary tumor with vascular invasion or multiple tumors none more than 5 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pT3a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Liver cancer with multiple tumors more than 5 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pT3b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Liver cancer with single tumor or multiple tumors of any size involving a major branch of the portal vein or hepatic vein. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Liver cancer with tumor(s) with direct invasion of adjacent organs other than the gallbladder or with perforation of visceral peritoneum. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of liver cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Liver Cancer pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Liver cancer in which regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Liver cancer with no regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Liver cancer with regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of liver cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for liver cancer. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Persistent Disease

value.value: A disease that does not go to remission despite treatment.

label.value: AIDS-Related Primary Effusion Lymphoma

value.value: Primary effusion lymphoma occurring in HIV-positive patients.

label.value: Liver Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Liver cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of liver cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Liver Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of liver cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Liver Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Liver cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Liver Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Liver cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: ABTB2 Gene

value.value: This gene may play a role in hepatocyte growth.

label.value: ABTB2 wt Allele

value.value: Human ABTB2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 11p13 and is approximately 250 kb in length. This allele, which encodes ankyrin repeat and BTB/POZ domain-containing protein 2, may be involved in the regulation of hepatocyte growth. Aberrant expression of the gene may be involved in leukemia relapse.

label.value: Ankyrin Repeat and BTB/POZ Domain-Containing Protein 2

value.value: Ankyrin repeat and BTB/POZ domain-containing protein 2 (839 aa, ~93 kDa) is encoded by the human ABTB2 gene. This protein may play a role in the growth of hepatocytes.

label.value: Acute Myeloid Leukemia with inv(16)(p13.1q22); CBFB-MYH11

value.value: Acute myeloid leukemia characterized by the presence of abnormal bone marrow eosinophils and the characteristic cytogenetic abnormality inv(16)(p13.1q22) which results in the expression of the fusion protein CBFB-MYH11.

label.value: Stage III Hepatocellular Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage III includes: IIIA: (T3a, N0, M0); IIIB: (T3b, N0, M0); IIIC: (T4, N0, M0). T3a: Multiple tumors more than 5 cm. T3b: Single tumor or multiple tumors of any size involving a major branch of the portal vein or hepatic vein.  T4: Tumors(s) with direct invasion of adjacent organs other than the gallbladder or with perforation of visceral peritoneum. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Hepatocellular Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IV includes: IVA: (Any T, N1, M0); IVB: (Any T, Any N, M1). N1: Regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis.  M1: Distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of intrahepatic bile duct cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  This is a novel staging system and applies only to intrahepatic cholangiocarcinomas and the rare combined hepatocellular and cholangiocarcinomas.  Pure hepatocellular carcinomas are not included in this classification. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of intrahepatic bile duct cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Complete pathologic staging consists of evaluation of the primary tumor, including tumor number, involvement of local regional lymph nodes, and the presence or absence of vascular invasion. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of intrahepatic bile duct cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer pTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ (intraductal tumor). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Intrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Intrahepatic bile duct cancer with solitary tumor without vascular invasion. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
